equence/default` with minimal bundle `change/mode/risk_tier/evidence_paths_or_diff_scope/findings_contract/retry_policy` over all changed files under `new/`, touched true-baseline vendor files, `design.md`, `specs/**/*.md`, and the generated runtime evidence; require verifier invocation via shell command entry using template id `verify-reviewer-shell-v1`, write normalized local review JSON to `openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/verification/implementation-subagent-review.json`, run mandatory `STRICT` Gemini second opinion through runner contract `gemini-capture`, write raw/report outputs to `openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/verification/implementation-gemini-raw.json` and `openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/verification/implementation-gemini-report.json`, apply fallback (`input_raw_path -> report_path`) if raw exists without report, route blocking findings through `openspec-repair-change`, and record the resolved command in `openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/verification/implementation-review-command.txt`.\n- [ ] 4.2 Once true-baseline verification passes, archive `port-old-to-new-ls2k0300-library` only as superseded history without syncing its specs, and keep the new retarget change as the only candidate for future spec sync or archive acceptance.\n- [ ] 4.3 [Checkpoint] Run verifier-subagent local review for implementation verification report and superseded-change closure using `verify-sequence/default`; write normalized local review JSON and ensure each rerun uses a fresh verifier instance (no inherited memory). If Gemini is required by risk tier or explicit dual gate, run logical runner contract `gemini-capture`, write both raw and normalized reports, and if primary execution fails after writing raw, run recovery (`input_raw_path -> report_path`) before blocking. Record resolved Linux/Windows command in execution evidence, not in task policy prose.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"c