openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/verification/artifact-subagent-review.raw.jsonl:52:{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"LS2K0300_Library/LS2K300_Library|\\\\.hpp|zf_common_headfile\\\\.hpp|wrapper-heavy|C-style|purely C|cv::Mat|Pit_timer|wait_image_refresh|rgay_image|imu_type|clear_count|exp_light|supersed\\\" openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library -S\"","aggregated_output":"openspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:3:The source system remains the TC264 bare-metal application under `old/`, with the same legacy control split already identified in the superseded change:\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:15:What changed is the target baseline. The completed change `port-old-to-new-ls2k0300-library` aligned against `LS2K0300_Library/LS2K300_Library/Seekfree_LS2K0300_Opensource_Library`, but the actual vendor baseline is `true_LS2K0300_Library/Seekfree_LS2K0300_Opensource_Library`.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:20:  - `.hpp` headers\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:26:  - wrapper-light, mixed C/C++ APIs rather than the superseded wrapper-heavy object layer\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:29:  - `zf_device_uvc` exposed as `uvc_camera_init`, `wait_image_refresh`, `rgay_image`, and `cv::Mat` image globals\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:30:  - `pit_ms_init` plus `Pit_timer` / `std::function` callback wiring, but still without a project-owned symmetric stop contract\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:32:Reference alignment mode is `adapt`, not `replicate`. Legacy control/perception logic is still the asset to preserve, but the real LS2K0300 stack offers materially different lifecycle and device contracts than the superseded wrapper-