ign.md:124:- Treating the superseded `LS2K0300_Library/LS2K300_Library/...` tree as an accepted alias of the real target.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:125:- Syncing the superseded change's specs as the accepted contract for the real port.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:131:### Decision 1: Treat the new work as a superseding retarget, not an in-place rewrite of the completed change\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:143:- Option B: Create a new change that explicitly supersedes the prior target selection.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:168:- If implementation or verification still points to `LS2K0300_Library/LS2K300_Library/...`, the retarget is blocked.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:169:- If archive/sync handling would promote the superseded change as the accepted spec source for the real target, the workflow must stop and route back to artifact repair.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:193:Option B. `new/` remains the owned workspace, but every vendor-root assumption is reset to the true library tree. The workspace SHALL not compile source files that only exist in the superseded baseline.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:208:- If the build graph references `zf_driver_file_buffer.cpp`, `zf_driver_file_string.cpp`, `zf_driver_pit_fd.cpp`, `zf_device_imu.cpp`, or other superseded-only source files, the build contract is invalid.\nopenspec/changes/retarget-port-to-true-ls2k0300-library/design.md:217:The real baseline exposes device access through `.h`-named headers, many free functions and globals, plus some direct C++ types/classes such as `std::function`, `cv::Mat`, and `Pit_timer`. Directly binding those APIs inside public adapters would preserve the existing decoupling at the port boundary, but it would still make platform 