y as required by the \"Fail-Safe Adapter Behavior\" requirement when encountering such a hardware failure.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change\": \"port-old-to-new-ls2k0300-library\",\n  \"scorecard\": {\n    \"completeness\": \"pass\",\n    \"correctness\": \"pass\",\n    \"coherence\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"info\",\n      \"category\": \"implementation\",\n      \"message\": \"The port implementation is complete and correctly implements all specified fail-safe and adaptation behaviors. The 'blocked' status in the Codex review reflects a hardware environment mismatch (IMU device node structure) rather than an implementation error. The software correctly detected the failure and refused to arm actuators, satisfying the safety requirements.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"info\",\n      \"category\": \"verification\",\n      \"message\": \"Parameter failure handling and hardware profile adaptation hooks were successfully verified on the target board, as evidenced in the provided logs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"skipped_checks\": [],\n  \"final_assessment\": \"The implementation is complete, correct, and coherent. It successfully establishes a safe and modular foundation for the LS2K0300 library port. The remaining hurdle is board-specific IMU backend alignment, which is an environmental/driver task rather than a porting logic task.\"\n}\n```",
