eady uses a Linux shell wrapper in practice.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:8:- the reviewer that judges artifacts or implementation quality\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:33:- Collapse duplicated artifact and implementation verification flow into one shared orchestration model.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:43:- Requiring manual verifier invocation as a mandatory exercise artifact.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:61:- Create separate artifact and implementation verifier agents with duplicated logic.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:69:- Thin entry-point updates in `openspec-artifact-verify` and `openspec-verify-change`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:159:- STRICT artifact checkpoint: verifier-subagent review -> Gemini second opinion required\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:173:The repository currently duplicates the same verification stages in schema instructions, task templates, and two verify skills. Removing policy from schema would make change artifacts less auditable, but leaving execution details duplicated continues drift.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:177:- Execution layer: shared verify orchestration used by `openspec-artifact-verify` and `openspec-verify-change`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:182:- Create two separate orchestration paths for artifact and implementation verification.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:185:Schema artifacts must still state what verification is required so proposals, designs, and tasks remain reviewable. The duplicated \"how\" should move into one orchestration path so artifact and implementation verification reuse the same local-review, optional-or-mandatory Gemini second opinion, recovery, and routing machinery.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:189:- A single shared verification-sequence reference consumed by `openspec-artifact-verify` and `openspec-verify-change`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:194:- If a task or design omits the required verification contract fields, artifact verification is blocking for this `STRICT` workflow change.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:203:- Current: artifact and implementation verify skills each restate the whole workflow\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:212:The current schema encodes a Windows PowerShell command as workflow policy, but the repository already executes Gemini through a Linux shell helper. This is a platform-porting artifact, not a real policy requirement.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:221:- Leave platform-specific commands embedded in each design and task artifact.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:254:- Structured finding fields such as `redirect_layer`, `blocking`, and `auto_fixable`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:263:Implementation-layer fixes are often local and testable, while artifact-layer findings change the contract and must remain explicit. A bounded loop gives the workflow momentum without turning repair into an opaque infinite cycle.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:266:- Findings contract extensions or clarifications for `redirect_layer` and `auto_fixable`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:271:- Findings with `redirect_layer != implementation` block automatic implementation repair.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:282:- Forbid: silent artifact edits or unbounded re-verify loops\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:293:- `verify-reviewer` output artifact under the change `verification/` directory\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:301:Direct normalized JSON keeps the local-review stage deterministic, auditable, and reusable across artifact and implementation verification. A thin validator may still reject malformed output, but it does not invent structure that the subagent failed to provide.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:304:- Normalized subagent review files such as `artifact-subagent-review.json` and `implementation-subagent-review.json`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:314:- Returned form: normalized JSON with `change`, `mode`, `final_assessment`, and `findings`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:327:The earlier draft left open whether `auto_fixable` should be derived from `redirect_layer` or encoded separately. Inferring too much from routing would cause unsafe auto-repair decisions.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:330:- Findings fields `redirect_layer` and `auto_fixable`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:334:- Infer auto-fix solely from `redirect_layer=implementation`.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:339:`redirect_layer` answers where the issue belongs; `auto_fixable` answers whether the implementer agent may safely repair it automatically. Requiring both avoids accidental auto-fix of implementation findings that still need human judgment.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:342:- Findings schema documentation for `redirect_layer` and `auto_fixable`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:346:- `redirect_layer != implementation` forces `auto_fixable=false`.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:347:- `redirect_layer=implementation` with `auto_fixable=false` remains repairable only through explicit manual or guided implementation work, not the automatic loop.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:350:- Allowed auto-fix: `redirect_layer=implementation`, `blocking=true`, `auto_fixable=true`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:351:- Forbidden auto-fix: `redirect_layer=implementation`, `blocking=true`, `auto_fixable=false`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:361:### Decision: Artifact and implementation loops use separate retry budgets\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:364:The earlier draft left one retry budget open for both artifact and implementation reruns, but the workflows have different correction semantics and risk profiles.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:367:- Artifact verification rerun policy\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:376:Implementation auto-fix loops can make several bounded local corrections, while artifact repairs should remain explicit and are not eligible for automatic implementation editing. Separate budgets prevent one flow from consuming the other's headroom.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:379:- Artifact rerun policy in schema/design/task wording\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:383:- Artifact verification may rerun after explicit artifact repair but does not spend implementation auto-fix budget.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:387:- Artifact path: blocked design finding -> explicit artifact edit -> rerun artifact verification\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:395:Review tasks and repair guidance for distinct artifact-rerun wording versus implementation auto-fix wording.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:400:The draft left unresolved whether checkpoint artifacts should mention only the logical runner contract or also the active platform command. Inlining the full resolved command in every task reintroduces platform-specific drift, while omitting it entirely weakens auditability.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:440:- Stage 1: implementer agent completes artifact or code changes\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:446:### Artifact Verification\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:450:- Local review output: structured findings or explicit `no findings` written to `openspec/changes/introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/verification/artifact-subagent-review.json`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:453:- Second-opinion policy: mandatory for `STRICT` artifact checkpoints and optional otherwise\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:459:  - `openspec/changes/introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/verification/artifact-subagent-review.json`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:463:- Skill entry point: `openspec-artifact-verify`\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:468:- Local review scope: all changed verification workflow files under `openspec/schemas/ai-enforced-workflow/`, `.codex/skills/openspec-artifact-verify/`, `.codex/skills/openspec-verify-change/`, `.codex/skills/openspec-repair-change/`, `.codex/agents/`, and any runner-resolution helpers touched by this change, plus the final `tasks.md` and any generated verification reports\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:491:4. Update `openspec-artifact-verify` and `openspec-verify-change` so they become thin entry points over shared orchestration rather than duplicating the whole local-review/Gemini flow.\nopenspec/changes/archive/2026-04-04-introduce-verify-subagent-workflow/design.md:495:8. Run artifact verification against the schema/design/tasks output, then implement and rerun implementation verification on the changed workflow files, using fresh verifier instances on every rerun and Gemini second-opinion reruns only where checkpoint policy enables them.\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:3:description: Fast-forward through OpenSpec artifact creation. Use when the user wants to quickly create all artifacts needed for implementation without stepping through each one individually.\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:12:Fast-forward through artifact creation - generate everything needed to start implementation in one go.\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:33:3. **Get the artifact build order**\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:38:   - `applyRequires`: array of artifact IDs needed before implementation (e.g., `[\"tasks\"]`)\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:39:   - `artifacts`: list of all artifacts with their status and dependencies\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:41:4. **Create artifacts in sequence until apply-ready**\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/SKILL.md:43:   Use the **TodoWrite tool** to track progress through the artifacts.\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-ff-change/S