ange and generate all artifacts in one step.\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:14:I'll create a change with artifacts:\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:42:3. **Get the artifact build order**\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:47:   - `applyRequires`: array of artifact IDs needed before implementation (e.g., `[\"tasks\"]`)\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:48:   - `artifacts`: list of all artifacts with their status and dependencies\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:50:4. **Create artifacts in sequence until apply-ready**\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:52:   Use the **TodoWrite tool** to track progress through the artifacts.\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:54:   Loop through artifacts in dependency order (artifacts with no pending dependencies first):\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:56:   a. **For each artifact that is `ready` (dependencies satisfied)**:\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:59:        openspec instructions <artifact-id> --change \"<name>\" --json\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:63:        - `rules`: Artifact-specific rules (constraints for you - do NOT include in output)\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:65:        - `instruction`: Schema-specific guidance for this artifact type\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:66:        - `outputPath`: Where to write the artifact\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:67:        - `dependencies`: Completed artifacts to read for context\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:69:      - Create the artifact file using `template` as the structure\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:71:      - Show brief progress: \"Created <artifact-id>\"\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:73:   b. **Continue until all `applyRequires` artifacts are complete**\r\n.codex/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md:74:      - After creating each artifact, re-run `openspec status --change \"<name>\" --json`\r\n.cod